parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusting of the master brake cylinder can lead to extended stopping distances, increasing the risk of accidents and compromising vehicle safety.
symptoms: brake pedal feels soft or mushy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the Anti-Lock Braking System (ABS) can cause the brakes to engage unnecessarily, leading to increased stopping distances, loss of cruise control, and potentially even a fire hazard.
symptoms: feeling of strain on the truck

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of electrical wiring can cause a vehicle fire, resulting in damage to the vehicle and potentially harm to occupants.
symptoms: Flames or sparks from under the dashboard
wiring damage on the driver-side fender wall
intermittent stalling of the vehicle while driving

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall while driving, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Intermittent stalling of the vehicle while driving
replacement of ignition and ignition coil does not resolve the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning idle air control valve can cause the engine to idle excessively high, leading to unintended acceleration, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: accelerator pedal stuck at full throttle.
